item.title: Please Read
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

[quote=“ilikecheese1231, post:10, topic:409483”][quote author=zyle1992 link=topic=510762.msg3706454#msg3706454 date=1313075293]
Visit: http://www.canyouseeme.org/
Type in the port into the box
Click “Check”
If it says “Error: I could not see your service on %s on port (43594)” then the port isn’t forwarded correctly.
[/quote]
Error: I could not see your service on 64.231.207.224 on port (43594)
Reason: Connection timed out thats what it says so it not pwed properly?[/quote]

Yes. It is not forwarded correctly. There are many things that could affect it. There are usually 3 levels of protection. From ISP->Router->Computer. I suggest going to portforward.com and looking at the guide for your specific router.
